title: Basis for exterior algebras

If $$e_1,\dots,e_m$$ is a basis for $$V,$$ then

$$
\{e_{i_1\cdots i_k}\coloneqq e_{i_1}\wedge\dots\wedge e_{i_k} \mid
1 \le i_1 < \dots < i_k < j \le m\}
$$

is a basis for $$\Lambda_k V,$$ so $$\dim\Lambda_k V=\binom m k.$$ We have $$\Lambda_0 V=\R$$ and $$\Lambda_m V\cong\R$$ and for $$k>m$$ we have $$\Lambda_k V=0,$$ so $$\dim\Lambda_* V=2^m.$$